<p>The Trump administration plans to deploy U.S. troops to Nigeria to train and advise Nigeria’s military as it fights Islamist militant groups, according to a U.S. official.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/v2wLnnuYphbxw65k33MWHIKsOsMOTBhZNC8Taw995OiN3VrM4qsfl3U7Zo1xRNcmNISaZapUTP2wEBQGKQg1BGFrBg4q9aDDLnTMeZQPwzSEOODb4Bo67FhOSR9RlPT46t4wfX8NrbL3wCcON5CbSwW-tqnGwpB-q-OyLo_gv3J7HB7S23ygdXrKiSYOUKgt-jVPDWcvAz3P38mCd6gGUw6_3oTCNVV25NOQpHpZLkwl7XWF5z6I2Kv5tnc2uUGCxOtP3hbomPifnEvzKg' alt='The seal is seen on a podium at the Pentagon in Washington before Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth speaks, Dec. 10, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Arrival window: One report says the troops could arrive in the coming weeks.</li><li>Operational coordination: The training and technical guidance aim to help Nigerian forces better synchronize air strikes with ground operations.</li><li>Militant groups cited: Anadolu Agency said the effort targets Boko Haram and other Islamist groups.</li><li>Recent U.S. action: The plan surfaced weeks after President Trump ordered air strikes against what he described as Islamic State targets.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. official (Trump administration): A U.S. official said the United States plans to send about 200 troops to Nigeria on a training mission, calling it a limited deployment. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/us-to-send-200-troops-to-nigeria-to-train-african-nations-military'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Firstpost report: Firstpost focused on the operational aim: using training and technical guidance to help Nigerian forces coordinate air and ground operations more effectively. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-to-deploy-200-troops-to-train-nigerian-army-in-its-battle-against-jihadist-groups-13978435.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Anadolu Agency report: Anadolu Agency said a U.S. military official confirmed the deployment, which would include logistical support as well as training, for Nigeria’s campaign against Boko Haram and other Islamist groups. (<a href='https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/us-military-confirms-deployment-of-small-team-to-nigeria/3819721'>Anadolu Agency</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-us-military-nigeria-troops-soldiers-trump/'>Trump administration will send 200 U.S. troops to Nigeria</a> - theglobeandmail.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/us-to-send-200-troops-to-nigeria-to-train-african-nations-military'>US to send 200 troops to Nigeria to train African nation&#x27;s military</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/us-to-send-200-troops-to-nigeria-to-train-african-nation%27s-military'>U.S. to send 200 troops to Nigeria to train African nation&#x27;s military</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-to-deploy-200-troops-to-train-nigerian-army-in-its-battle-against-jihadist-groups-13978435.html'>US to deploy 200 troops to train Nigerian army in its battle against jihadist groups</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/us-military-confirms-deployment-of-small-team-to-nigeria/3819721'>A United States military official confirms that the U.S. will deploy 200 soldiers to Nigeria to help train the Nigerian military and provide logistical support against Boko Haram and other Islamic terrorist groups.</a> - aa.com.tr</li></ul>